= Non-Qubes-Whonix System Requirements =
== Minimum ==
* 1 GB free RAM (with Whonix-Gateway lowered to 256 MB). <ref>
The Whonix-Gateway can work with as low as 256 MB RAM, but resource intensive operations like kernel package upgrades that rebuild the initrd might leave the virtual machine in a frozen state. 
</ref>
* 10 GB free hard drive space.

== Recommended ==
* Additional hard drive space when installing applications into the Whonix-Workstation.
* A CPU with [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X86_virtualization#AMD_virtualization_.28AMD-V.29 AMD-V] or Intel [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X86_virtualization#Intel_virtualization_.28VT-x.29 VT-x].

== For Best Performance ==
* A solid state drive (SSD).
* Additional RAM to dedicate to the Whonix-Workstation when multitasking.

== Notes ==
* Whonix-Workstation can be run with 196 MB RAM when not using a desktop environment.
* For low memory and console-only configurations, see [[Desktop#RAM_Adjusted_Desktop_Starter|Ram Adjusted Desktop Starter]].
* If you do not have AMD-V or Intel VT-x and you encounter a PAE or "{{Code2|VERR_SSM_FIELD_NOT_CONSECUTIVE}}" error, please read [[Starting Whonix#PAE crash|PAE Crash]] for a workaround.
* Linux users with low RAM might save some RAM on the host if they use a lighter desktop environment like Xfce or LXDE, rather than KDE, GNOME etc.

