== Minimum (Qubes 3.X) ==
* A 64-bit Intel or AMD processor (x86_64 aka x64 aka AMD64). <ref> Qubes system requirements are directly sourced from https://www.qubes-os.org/doc/system-requirements/</ref>
* 4 GB RAM.
* 32 GB disk space.
* Legacy boot mode (required for R3.0 and earlier; UEFI is supported beginning with R3.1).

== Minimum (Qubes 4.X) ==
* As per Qubes 3.X minimum requirements above, ''plus'' Intel VT-x with [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Level_Address_Translation#Extended_Page_Tables EPT] or AMD-V with [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Level_Address_Translation#Rapid_Virtualization_Indexing RVI].

== Recommended ==
* A fast SSD (strongly recommended).
* Intel IGP (strongly preferred).
** Nvidia GPUs may require significant troubleshooting.
** ATI GPUs have not been formally tested (but see the [https://www.qubes-os.org/hcl/ Hardware Compatibility List]).
* Intel VT-x or AMD-V (required for running HVM domains, such as Windows-based AppVMs).
* Intel VT-d or AMD-Vi (aka AMD IOMMU) (required for effective isolation of network VMs and PCI passthrough).
* TPM with proper BIOS support (required for Anti Evil Maid).
*  8 GB+ RAM. <ref>Users report problems in creating DisposableVMs and running multiple VMs in parallel with only 4 GB RAM.</ref>
* A non-USB keyboard or multiple USB controllers to enable creation of a USB VM. <ref>To prevent malicious compromise of dom0 via USB mice, keyboards or other USB devices.</ref>


Before purchasing any hardware specifically for Qubes, always check the [https://www.qubes-os.org/hcl/ hardware compatibility list] first for suitable models.

